cs.IR, cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.DL

This paper deals with text mining techniques for document clustering and visualization, which are commonly studied in the fields of information retrieval (cs.IR), computational linguistics (cs.CL), machine learning (cs.LG, cs.AI), and deep learning (cs.DL). The focus on biomedical documents may also suggest a potential fit with sub-categories such as cs.CB (computational biology) or cs.DB (databases), but the emphasis on text-based analysis makes the former less likely and the absence of explicit database-related methods or results makes the latter less probable.
